<h1 data-start="1492" data-end="1516">Core design principles</h1>
<ul data-start="1518" data-end="2453">
<li data-start="1518" data-end="1736">
<p data-start="1520" data-end="1736"><strong data-start="1520" data-end="1549">Function-based collectors</strong>: each <code data-start="1556" data-end="1574">Collectors/*.ps1</code> exports exactly one <code data-start="1595" data-end="1610">Get-SAT&lt;Area&gt;</code> function that returns a <em data-start="1635" data-end="1642">plain</em> <code data-start="1643" data-end="1656">[hashtable]</code> (fast, property bag). The orchestrator merges hashtables into a single dataset.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1737" data-end="1964">
<p data-start="1739" data-end="1964"><strong data-start="1739" data-end="1760">Back-compat first</strong>: prefer CIM/WMI/<code data-start="1777" data-end="1784">netsh</code> fallbacks when role modules aren’t present (e.g., DNS <code data-start="1839" data-end="1858">root\MicrosoftDNS</code>, DHCP <code data-start="1865" data-end="1891">netsh dhcp server export</code>, roles via <code data-start="1903" data-end="1924">Win32_ServerFeature</code>). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/dns/overview-of-using-the-dns-wmi-provider?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/dns/overview-of-using-the-dns-wmi-provider?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between absolute" style="opacity: 0; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+3</span></span><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+3</span></span><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between absolute" style="opacity: 0; transform: translateX(10%);"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+3</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1965" data-end="2115">
<p data-start="1967" data-end="2115"><strong data-start="1967" data-end="2003">Parallel execution (PS 4.0-safe)</strong>: use <strong data-start="2009" data-end="2027">runspace pools</strong> (not <code data-start="2033" data-end="2059">ForEach-Object -Parallel</code>, which is PS 7+). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/scripting/developer/hosting/runspace-samples?view=powershell-7.5&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/scripting/developer/hosting/runspace-samples?view=powershell-7.5&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2116" data-end="2191">
<p data-start="2118" data-end="2191"><strong data-start="2118" data-end="2149">Verbose, structured logging</strong>: timestamped console + optional JSON log.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2192" data-end="2255">
<p data-start="2194" data-end="2255"><strong data-start="2194" data-end="2220">Idempotent / read-only</strong>: collectors must not modify state.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2256" data-end="2350">
<p data-start="2258" data-end="2350"><strong data-start="2258" data-end="2276">Report outputs</strong>: <code data-start="2278" data-end="2294">out/summary.md</code>, <code data-start="2296" data-end="2313">out/report.html</code>, <code data-start="2315" data-end="2330">out/data.json</code>, and granular CSVs.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2351" data-end="2453">
<p data-start="2353" data-end="2453"><strong data-start="2353" data-end="2370">Quality gates</strong>: Pester v5 tests and PSScriptAnalyzer in CI. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://pester.dev/docs/migrations/breaking-changes-in-v5?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://pester.dev/docs/migrations/breaking-changes-in-v5?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">pester.dev</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+2</span></span><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between absolute" style="opacity: 0; transform: translateX(10%);"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">GitHub</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+2</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
