<p data-start="17154" data-end="17224">(PSScriptAnalyzer module ref. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/psscriptanalyzer/?view=ps-modules&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/psscriptanalyzer/?view=ps-modules&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span>)</p>
<hr data-start="17226" data-end="17229">
<h1 data-start="17231" data-end="17281">What the report tells you (migration-ready cues)</h1>
<ul data-start="17283" data-end="17916">
<li data-start="17283" data-end="17435">
<p data-start="17285" data-end="17435"><strong data-start="17285" data-end="17303">Role inventory</strong> → maps to <em data-start="17314" data-end="17336">what needs migrating</em> (e.g., DNS zones, DHCP scopes/leases, IIS sites/app pools, Hyper-V VMs, file shares, cert stores).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="17436" data-end="17551">
<p data-start="17438" data-end="17551"><strong data-start="17438" data-end="17460">Directory services</strong> (if AD DS) → forest/domain mode, FSMO roles (read-only), SYSVOL replication (DFSR vs FRS).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="17552" data-end="17716">
<p data-start="17554" data-end="17716"><strong data-start="17554" data-end="17569">Data volume</strong> → counts (zones, scopes, sites, VMs), sizes (IIS content, shared folders), and <em data-start="17649" data-end="17663">dependencies</em> (forwarders, DHCP options, IIS bindings, cert refs).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="17717" data-end="17838">
<p data-start="17719" data-end="17838"><strong data-start="17719" data-end="17736">Compatibility</strong> → flags where fallback was used (e.g., “Win32_ServerFeature fallback”) so you know confidence levels.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="17839" data-end="17916">
<p data-start="17841" data-end="17916"><strong data-start="17841" data-end="17865">Remoting/permissions</strong> → note if WinRM disabled (cannot do remote audit).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="17918" data-end="17921">
<h1 data-start="17923" data-end="17953">Why these choices are robust</h1>
<ul data-start="17955" data-end="18664">
<li data-start="17955" data-end="18203">
<p data-start="17957" data-end="18203"><strong data-start="17957" data-end="17982">ServerManager cmdlets</strong> (<code data-start="17984" data-end="18004">Get-WindowsFeature</code>) are the authoritative way to enumerate server roles on Windows Server; where missing, WMI <code data-start="18096" data-end="18117">Win32_ServerFeature</code> returns installed roles (not available ones). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/servermanager/get-windowsfeature?view=windowsserver2025-ps&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/servermanager/get-windowsfeature?view=windowsserver2025-ps&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="18204" data-end="18359">
<p data-start="18206" data-end="18359"><strong data-start="18206" data-end="18226">DNS WMI provider</strong> offers stable read access back to 2012; the <code data-start="18271" data-end="18282">DnsServer</code> module is preferred on newer builds. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/dns/overview-of-using-the-dns-wmi-provider?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/dns/overview-of-using-the-dns-wmi-provider?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="18360" data-end="18531">
<p data-start="18362" data-end="18531"><strong data-start="18362" data-end="18370">DHCP</strong>: <code data-start="18372" data-end="18384">DhcpServer</code> module on modern servers; <code data-start="18411" data-end="18437">netsh dhcp server export</code> remains a supported fallback for inventory/migration. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/dhcpserver/export-dhcpserver?view=windowsserver2025-ps&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/dhcpserver/export-dhcpserver?view=windowsserver2025-ps&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="18532" data-end="18664">
<p data-start="18534" data-end="18664"><strong data-start="18534" data-end="18549">Parallelism</strong> via <strong data-start="18554" data-end="18567">runspaces</strong> ensures speed on new servers <em data-start="18597" data-end="18602">and</em> works down to PS 4.0. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/scripting/developer/hosting/runspace-samples?view=powershell-7.5&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/scripting/developer/hosting/runspace-samples?view=powershell-7.5&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="18666" data-end="18669">
