<hr data-start="15793" data-end="15796">
<h2 data-start="15798" data-end="15806">Notes</h2>
<ul data-start="15808" data-end="16266">
<li data-start="15808" data-end="15924">
<p data-start="15810" data-end="15924">All collectors return hashtables; the orchestrator merges them, so the report can export consistently shaped CSVs.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="15925" data-end="16131">
<p data-start="15927" data-end="16131">Fallbacks are intentionally conservative (e.g., Hyper-V WMI doesn’t try to traverse every association) to stay fast and PS 4.0-safe; you can deepen later if you need NIC/switch/disks via WMI associations.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="16132" data-end="16266">
<p data-start="16134" data-end="16266">Everything is verbose-first (<code data-start="16163" data-end="16174">Write-Log</code> → <code data-start="16177" data-end="16192">Write-Verbose</code>/<code data-start="16193" data-end="16208">Write-Warning</code>/<code data-start="16209" data-end="16222">Write-Error</code>) so you can trace each step on the console.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="16268" data-end="16296">If you want, I can also add:</p>
<ul data-start="16297" data-end="16526">
<li data-start="16297" data-end="16380">
<p data-start="16299" data-end="16380">File Shares/NTFS ACL collector (SMB + <code data-start="16337" data-end="16351">Get-SmbShare</code> → WMI/<code data-start="16358" data-end="16369">net share</code> fallback).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="16381" data-end="16453">
<p data-start="16383" data-end="16453">Certificate store deep-dive (thumbprints, expiry, bindings cross-ref).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="16454" data-end="16526">
<p data-start="16456" data-end="16526">AD DS collector (forest/domain levels, FSMO, SYSVOL replication mode).</p>
</li>
</ul>
