  [CmdletBinding()]
  param([Parameter(Mandatory)] [array]$Tasks, [int]$Throttle = [Environment]::ProcessorCount)

  Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Management.Automation
  $iss = [System.Management.Automation.Runspaces.InitialSessionState]::CreateDefault()
  $mod = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot '..\ServerAuditToolkitV2.psd1'
  $iss.ImportPSModule($mod)
  $pool = [runspacefactory]::CreateRunspacePool(1,$Throttle,$iss,$host)
  $pool.ApartmentState = 'MTA'
  $pool.Open()

  $worker = {
    param($fn,$targets,$cap,$verbosePref)
    &amp; $fn -ComputerName $targets -Capability $cap -Verbose:$verbosePref
  }.ToString()

  $handles = @()
  foreach ($t in $Tasks) {
    $ps = [powershell]::Create()
    $ps.RunspacePool = $pool
    $null = $ps.AddScript($worker).AddArgument($t.Name)
    foreach ($a in $t.Args) { $null = $ps.AddArgument($a) }
    $null = $ps.AddArgument($VerbosePreference)
    $handles += [pscustomobject]@{ Name=$t.Name; PS=$ps; Handle=$ps.BeginInvoke() }
  }

  $out = @()
  foreach ($h in $handles) {
    $data = $h.PS.EndInvoke($h.Handle)
    $out += [pscustomobject]@{ Name=$h.Name; Data=$data }
    $h.PS.Dispose()
  }
  $pool.Close(); $pool.Dispose()
  return $out
}
</span></code></div></div></pre>
<ol start="2" data-start="19857" data-end="20845">
<li data-start="19857" data-end="20182">
<p data-start="19860" data-end="20182">Credentials &amp; session options<br data-start="19889" data-end="19892">
Add <code data-start="19896" data-end="19909">-Credential</code> and optional <code data-start="19923" data-end="19939">-SessionOption</code> to <code data-start="19943" data-end="19963">Invoke-ServerAudit</code> and pass them to collectors. In collectors, call <code data-start="20013" data-end="20104">Invoke-Command -ComputerName $c -Credential $Credential -SessionOption $SessionOption ...</code>. For timeouts with CIM, consider <code data-start="20138" data-end="20181">New-CimSessionOption -OperationTimeoutSec</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="20184" data-end="20444">
<p data-start="20187" data-end="20444">Trim unnecessary JSON round-trips<br data-start="20220" data-end="20223">
Inside collectors you often do <code data-start="20254" data-end="20270">ConvertTo-Json</code>…<code data-start="20271" data-end="20289">ConvertFrom-Json</code> to “normalize” objects. It’s slower. PS Remoting already returns deserialized objects; prefer returning them directly. Reserve JSON only for final export.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="20446" data-end="20623">
<p data-start="20449" data-end="20623">Configurability<br data-start="20464" data-end="20467">
Add <code data-start="20471" data-end="20512">-IncludeCollectors / -ExcludeCollectors</code>, <code data-start="20514" data-end="20525">-Throttle</code>, <code data-start="20527" data-end="20541">-MaxHtmlRows</code>, and caps (<code data-start="20553" data-end="20573">-MaxTasksPerServer</code>, <code data-start="20575" data-end="20591">-MaxAclEntries</code>) to tune perf on large estates.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="20625" data-end="20820">
<p data-start="20628" data-end="20820">Better logging<br data-start="20642" data-end="20645">
Keep console verbose, but also add <code data-start="20680" data-end="20690">-LogPath</code> to emit <strong data-start="20699" data-end="20719">structured JSONL</strong> for SIEM ingestion (one line per event with <code data-start="20764" data-end="20775">Timestamp</code>, <code data-start="20777" data-end="20784">Level</code>, <code data-start="20786" data-end="20795">Message</code>, <code data-start="20797" data-end="20808">Collector</code>, <code data-start="20810" data-end="20818">Server</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="20822" data-end="20845">
<p data-start="20825" data-end="20845">Security &amp; privacy</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start="20846" data-end="21086">
<li data-start="20846" data-end="20975">
<p data-start="20848" data-end="20975">No secrets are collected, but consider a <strong data-start="20889" data-end="20908">redaction layer</strong> (e.g., hash MAC addresses, truncate SIDs) when <code data-start="20956" data-end="20965">-Redact</code> is set.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="20976" data-end="21086">
<p data-start="20978" data-end="21086">Sign your module (<code data-start="20996" data-end="21023">Set-AuthenticodeSignature</code>) and ship a <code data-start="21036" data-end="21044">README</code> section on execution policy &amp; signatures.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start="7" data-start="21088" data-end="21363">
<li data-start="21088" data-end="21314">
<p data-start="21091" data-end="21314">Report UX polish<br data-start="21107" data-end="21110">
If you can allow external JS, add lightweight client-side sorting/filtering (e.g., DataTables). If offline-only, embed a tiny search script. Consider an <code data-start="21263" data-end="21276">-SingleHtml</code> mode that inlines Bootstrap (no CDN).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="21316" data-end="21363">
<p data-start="21319" data-end="21363">Cross-references (big value for migration)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start="21364" data-end="21575">
<li data-start="21364" data-end="21417">
<p data-start="21366" data-end="21417">IIS HTTPS bindings → match <code data-start="21393" data-end="21405">Thumbprint</code> in certs.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="21418" data-end="21483">
<p data-start="21420" data-end="21483">SMB share paths → show backing <strong data-start="21451" data-end="21461">volume</strong> and <strong data-start="21466" data-end="21480">free space</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="21484" data-end="21575">
<p data-start="21486" data-end="21575">Hyper-V VHDX paths → show volume &amp; free space.<br data-start="21532" data-end="21535">
These become concrete “move plan” items.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start="9" data-start="21577" data-end="21951">
<li data-start="21577" data-end="21924">
<p data-start="21580" data-end="21924">Additional optional collectors (nice-to-haves)<br data-start="21626" data-end="21629">
Failover Clustering (roles/resources), DFS Namespaces/DFSR, Print Server, WSUS, AD CS (if present), Installed software inventory (Uninstall registry + <code data-start="21780" data-end="21795">Win32_Product</code> <strong data-start="21796" data-end="21803">not</strong> recommended), Services (startup mode, disabled/automatic), NTP/time source, and <strong data-start="21884" data-end="21904">GPO links on OUs</strong> (for AD readiness).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="21926" data-end="21951">
<p data-start="21930" data-end="21951">CI/CD and packaging</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start="21952" data-end="22214">
<li data-start="21952" data-end="22043">
<p data-start="21954" data-end="22043">Add a <strong data-start="21960" data-end="21980">release workflow</strong> to publish ZIP artifacts (module + scripts + sample report).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="22044" data-end="22134">
<p data-start="22046" data-end="22134">Optionally package to <strong data-start="22068" data-end="22090">PowerShell Gallery</strong> with semantic versioning and a CHANGELOG.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="22135" data-end="22214">
<p data-start="22137" data-end="22214">Add Pester coverage thresholds and run ScriptAnalyzer with your custom rules.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start="11" data-start="22216" data-end="22451">
<li data-start="22216" data-end="22451">
<p data-start="22220" data-end="22451">Permissions &amp; prerequisites doc<br data-start="22251" data-end="22254">
Document clearly what needs <strong data-start="22282" data-end="22297">local admin</strong> (IIS/appcmd, netsh, Hyper-V, SMB ACLs), and what works as “readers.” Include a small <code data-start="22383" data-end="22400">Test-SATPrereqs</code> that checks remoting, access, and module presence.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="22453" data-end="22456">
<p data-start="22458" data-end="22478">If you want, I can:</p>
<ul data-start="22479" data-end="22639">
<li data-start="22479" data-end="22520">
<p data-start="22481" data-end="22520">add <code data-start="22485" data-end="22498">-Credential</code> plumbing everywhere,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="22521" data-end="22597">
<p data-start="22523" data-end="22597">add the cross-reference logic (IIS→Certs, SMB/Hyper-V paths→Volumes), and</p>
</li>
<li data-start="22598" data-end="22639">
<p data-start="22600" data-end="22639">drop a release GitHub Actions workflow.</p>
</li>
</ul>
