<p data-start="5331" data-end="5580">A lightweight evaluator (<code data-start="5356" data-end="5379">Evaluate-SATReadiness</code>) loops units, evaluates rules (PowerShell expressions or a tiny DSL), and emits findings with <code data-start="5474" data-end="5484">Severity</code>, <code data-start="5486" data-end="5494">RuleId</code>, <code data-start="5496" data-end="5505">Message</code>. Show the top findings in the HTML and write <code data-start="5551" data-end="5579">out/readiness_findings.csv</code>.</p>
<h1 data-start="5582" data-end="5624">3) Cross-references that unlock accuracy</h1>
<ul data-start="5625" data-end="6169">
<li data-start="5625" data-end="5706">
<p data-start="5627" data-end="5706"><strong data-start="5627" data-end="5650">IIS ↔ Certificates:</strong> Resolve bindings to cert thumbprints (already modeled).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5707" data-end="5833">
<p data-start="5709" data-end="5833"><strong data-start="5709" data-end="5727">SMB ↔ Volumes:</strong> Map share paths to volumes (drive letter/prefix); attach <code data-start="5785" data-end="5795">SizeHint</code> (optional <code data-start="5806" data-end="5826">-EstimateShareSize</code> mode).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5834" data-end="5948">
<p data-start="5836" data-end="5948"><strong data-start="5836" data-end="5858">Hyper-V ↔ Storage:</strong> VHDX paths → volume size/free; flag pass-through disks, checkpoints, differencing chains.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5949" data-end="6064">
<p data-start="5951" data-end="6064"><strong data-start="5951" data-end="5979">Scheduled Tasks ↔ Files:</strong> Flag tasks where <code data-start="5997" data-end="6008">ActionExe</code> lives on a non-system volume or UNC (migration impact).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6065" data-end="6169">
<p data-start="6067" data-end="6169"><strong data-start="6067" data-end="6084">Local Admins:</strong> Surface local Administrators group membership as a dedicated MU for security review.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="6171" data-end="6220">4) Optional precision boosters (off by default)</h1>
<ul data-start="6221" data-end="6812">
<li data-start="6221" data-end="6378">
<p data-start="6223" data-end="6378"><code data-start="6223" data-end="6243">-EstimateShareSize</code>: For each share root, run a <strong data-start="6272" data-end="6282">capped</strong> directory walk to compute size (e.g., timeout or max file count); cache intermediate results.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6379" data-end="6513">
<p data-start="6381" data-end="6513"><code data-start="6381" data-end="6397">-ListListening</code>: Include listening ports (NetTCPIP or <code data-start="6436" data-end="6450">netstat -ano</code>) and attempt <strong data-start="6464" data-end="6479">best-effort</strong> process mapping (PS 5.1+ only).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6514" data-end="6812">
<p data-start="6516" data-end="6812"><code data-start="6516" data-end="6535">-PrinterDiscovery</code>: Add <strong data-start="6541" data-end="6559">Print Services</strong> collector (<code data-start="6571" data-end="6584">Get-Printer</code> → <code data-start="6587" data-end="6602">Win32_Printer</code>/PrintBRM hints) to list queues/ports/drivers so you know if print migration is needed. (Migration is typically via <strong data-start="6718" data-end="6747">PrintBRM/Print Management</strong>; we’re just inventorying.) <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/troubleshoot/windows-server/printing/back-up-restore-printers?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/troubleshoot/windows-server/printing/back-up-restore-printers?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="6814" data-end="6846">5) Destination “profile” flags</h1>
