<p data-start="7017" data-end="7026">Examples:</p>
<ul data-start="7027" data-end="7421">
<li data-start="7027" data-end="7144">
<p data-start="7029" data-end="7144">For <strong data-start="7033" data-end="7048">Azure Files</strong>: flag SMB shares with unsupported features (e.g., SMB encryption requirements vs planned tier).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7145" data-end="7278">
<p data-start="7147" data-end="7278">For <strong data-start="7151" data-end="7166">App Service</strong>: flag IIS sites using Windows-specific modules or COM objects (heuristics from modules and web.config parsing).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7279" data-end="7421">
<p data-start="7281" data-end="7421">For <strong data-start="7285" data-end="7295">WS2025</strong>: highlight roles with official migration guides and links (DHCP/DNS/IIS/WSUS/NPS/etc.). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/get-started/upgrade-migrate-roles-features" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/get-started/upgrade-migrate-roles-features" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="7423" data-end="7451">6) Confidence + provenance</h1>
<p data-start="7452" data-end="7702">Every MU gets a <strong data-start="7468" data-end="7482">Confidence</strong> (module=1.0, WMI=0.8, text scrape=0.6) and <strong data-start="7526" data-end="7538">Evidence</strong> entries listing collector + key fields. This makes the report auditable and lets you quickly spot anything discovered via fallback that merits manual verification.</p>
<h1 data-start="7704" data-end="7727">7) Baselines &amp; deltas</h1>
<p data-start="7728" data-end="7810">Add <code data-start="7732" data-end="7750">-Baseline &lt;file&gt;</code> to compare a new run to a prior <code data-start="7783" data-end="7796">data_*.json</code> and generate:</p>
<ul data-start="7811" data-end="7935">
<li data-start="7811" data-end="7858">
<p data-start="7813" data-end="7858"><code data-start="7813" data-end="7830">delta_units.csv</code> (Added/Removed/Changed MUs)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7859" data-end="7935">
<p data-start="7861" data-end="7935">“What changed since last run?” section in HTML (super useful mid-project).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="7937" data-end="7981">8) Role-specific depth (what WSMT implies)</h1>
<p data-start="7982" data-end="8124">Microsoft’s guidance and tools imply these specifics matter for migration readiness; you can extract them cleanly and show them in the report:</p>
<ul data-start="8126" data-end="9016">
<li data-start="8126" data-end="8289">
<p data-start="8128" data-end="8289"><strong data-start="8128" data-end="8136">DHCP</strong>: scopes, reservations, policies, options, <strong data-start="8179" data-end="8205">failover relationships</strong>. (MS has an up-to-date DHCP migration guide.) <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/networking/technologies/dhcp/migrate-dhcp-server?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/networking/technologies/dhcp/migrate-dhcp-server?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8290" data-end="8428">
<p data-start="8292" data-end="8428"><strong data-start="8292" data-end="8299">DNS</strong>: zone type (primary/AD-integrated/stub/secondary), replication scope, <strong data-start="8370" data-end="8390">aging/scavenging</strong>, forwarders/conditional forwarders.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8429" data-end="8664">
<p data-start="8431" data-end="8664"><strong data-start="8431" data-end="8438">IIS</strong>: sites/apps/bindings, AppPool CLR &amp; pipeline, auth providers, URL rewrite presence; when actually migrating, Microsoft recommends <strong data-start="8569" data-end="8583">Web Deploy</strong> — we’re just showing whether that’s a fit. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/iis/publish/using-web-deploy/use-the-web-deployment-tool?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/iis/publish/using-web-deploy/use-the-web-deployment-tool?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8665" data-end="8807">
<p data-start="8667" data-end="8807"><strong data-start="8667" data-end="8676">Print</strong>: enumerate queues/ports/drivers so you know if <strong data-start="8724" data-end="8753">PrintBRM/Print Management</strong> will be needed. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/troubleshoot/windows-server/printing/back-up-restore-printers?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/troubleshoot/windows-server/printing/back-up-restore-printers?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="8808" data-end="9016">
<p data-start="8810" data-end="9016"><strong data-start="8810" data-end="8818">File</strong>: shares, permissions snapshot, optional size estimate; for the actual move Microsoft now prefers <strong data-start="8916" data-end="8945">Storage Migration Service</strong> (again, we just identify/scope). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/get-started/upgrade-migrate-roles-features" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/get-started/upgrade-migrate-roles-features" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Microsoft Learn</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="9018" data-end="9047">9) Small HTML/report tweaks</h1>
<ul data-start="9048" data-end="9371">
<li data-start="9048" data-end="9155">
<p data-start="9050" data-end="9155">New <strong data-start="9054" data-end="9073">Migration Units</strong> section: counts per kind + CSV download per kind + top 10 findings (rule engine).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9156" data-end="9248">
<p data-start="9158" data-end="9248">Add a <strong data-start="9164" data-end="9186">Confidence heatmap</strong>: show how much of the inventory came from module vs fallback.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9249" data-end="9371">
<p data-start="9251" data-end="9371">Link each MU to its <strong data-start="9271" data-end="9283">evidence</strong> and <strong data-start="9288" data-end="9304">dependencies</strong> (e.g., click an IIS binding → scroll to the matching certificate).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-start="9373" data-end="9401">10) Fast path to implement</h1>
<ul data-start="9402" data-end="9742">
<li data-start="9402" data-end="9479">
<p data-start="9404" data-end="9479">Add two new functions: <code data-start="9427" data-end="9450">New-SATMigrationUnits</code> and <code data-start="9455" data-end="9478">Evaluate-SATReadiness</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9480" data-end="9585">
<p data-start="9482" data-end="9585">Call them at the end of <code data-start="9506" data-end="9526">Invoke-ServerAudit</code>, save <code data-start="9533" data-end="9555">migration_units.json</code> and <code data-start="9560" data-end="9584">readiness_findings.csv</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9586" data-end="9653">
<p data-start="9588" data-end="9653">Extend <code data-start="9595" data-end="9607">Report.ps1</code> to render “Migration Units” and top findings.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9654" data-end="9742">
<p data-start="9656" data-end="9742">Optional: add <code data-start="9670" data-end="9691">rules\readiness.yml</code> to repo and load it (or ship an embedded default).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="9744" data-end="9747">
<p data-start="9749" data-end="9776">If you like, I can wire in:</p>
<ul data-start="9777" data-end="9998">
<li data-start="9777" data-end="9875">
<p data-start="9779" data-end="9875">a <strong data-start="9781" data-end="9812">printer inventory collector</strong> (Print Management → <code data-start="9833" data-end="9846">Get-Printer</code> / <code data-start="9849" data-end="9864">Win32_Printer</code> fallback),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9876" data-end="9938">
<p data-start="9878" data-end="9938">the MU aggregator + rules engine (with a few starter rules),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9939" data-end="9998">
<p data-start="9941" data-end="9998">and the new HTML sections with findings + confidence bar.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10000" data-end="10161">This will make SATv2 laser-focused on <strong data-start="10038" data-end="10057">what to migrate</strong> and <strong data-start="10062" data-end="10083">how risky/complex</strong> each piece looks, while staying tool-agnostic about how you actually move it.</p>
