<h2 data-start="21778" data-end="21813">Optional next steps (quick wins)</h2>
<ul data-start="21814" data-end="22179">
<li data-start="21814" data-end="21974">
<p data-start="21816" data-end="21974">Add <code data-start="21820" data-end="21832">-RulesPath</code> to <code data-start="21836" data-end="21856">Invoke-ServerAudit</code> so you can point to a custom rules JSON per migration target (Azure, WS2025, etc.). Then load it instead of defaults.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="21975" data-end="22081">
<p data-start="21977" data-end="22081">Add a <strong data-start="21983" data-end="21997">delta mode</strong>: <code data-start="21999" data-end="22022">-Baseline &lt;data.json&gt;</code> → compute changed/added/removed MUs and surface in report.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="22082" data-end="22179">
<p data-start="22084" data-end="22179">Enrich rules over time (e.g., DHCP failover presence, IIS auth providers, Hyper-V checkpoints).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="22181" data-end="22263">If you want, I can add the <code data-start="22208" data-end="22220">-RulesPath</code> parameter and delta comparison wiring too.</p>
