rflow-hidden border-t transition-colors border-transparent"><section class="popover flex h-full w-full flex-col bg-transparent"><section class="relative flex min-h-0 flex-auto grow flex-col overflow-hidden"><div class="block h-auto"><div class="h-full w-full"><div class="flex h-full justify-center" style="margin: 0px 24px; padding-top: 4px;"><div class="z-0 flex w-full flex-col items-center"><div id="prosemirror-context-children"></div><div class="relative z-10 flex max-w-full h-fit" id="prosemirror-editor-container" style="padding-bottom: 4px;"><div class="_main_5jn6z_1 z-10 markdown prose dark:prose-invert contain-inline-size focus:outline-hidden bg-transparent ProseMirror" contenteditable="false" style="width: 2059px;" translate="no"><h1><span>ServerAuditToolkitV2 — Operations Runbook (TL;DR-friendly, detailed)</span></h1><p><span>This runbook explains how engineers set up, run, and contribute to </span><strong><span>ServerAuditToolkitV2</span></strong><span> (SATv2). The toolkit inventories Windows Servers (2025 → 2012 R2 / PS 4.0) and produces a </span><strong><span>migration‑readiness</span></strong><span> report with per‑area CSVs and a Bootstrap HTML dashboard. It identifies </span><strong><span>what needs to be migrated</span></strong><span> via “Migration Units” and flags issues with a rule engine.</span></p><p><span>Repo: </span><a disabled="true"><span>https://github.com/tonynash74/ServerAuditToolkitv2</span></a></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>1) Prerequisites</span></h2><p><strong><span>Environment</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Windows admin workstation or jump server with </span><strong><span>Windows PowerShell 4.0+</span></strong><span> (5.1 recommended)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Network reachability to targets (WinRM: TCP 5985/5986 if using HTTPS)</span></p></li><li><p><span>A browser to view HTML reports</span></p></li><li><p><span>Sufficient disk space for outputs (JSON/CSV/HTML)</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Permissions</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Run as </span><strong><span>local administrator</span></strong><span> on target servers (required for some collectors: IIS, Hyper‑V, SMB ACLs, netsh, DHCP export)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Access to </span><code><span>\\&lt;server&gt;\ADMIN$</span></code><span> for certain fallbacks (e.g., DHCP export)</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Tools</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Git (to clone)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Optional: VS Code + PowerShell extension (for dev/contrib)</span></p></li></ul><blockquote><p><span>The toolkit is </span><strong><span>read‑only</span></strong><span>. It does not change system state.</span></p></blockquote><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>2) Install &amp; Update</span></h2><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ4y ͼ3t" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼe"># Clone once</span></div><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">git</span> <span class="ͼd">clone</span> <span class="ͼd">https</span>://<span class="ͼd">github</span>.<span class="ͼd">com</span>/<span class="ͼd">tonynash74</span>/<span class="ͼd">ServerAuditToolkitv2</span>.<span class="ͼd">git</span></div><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">cd</span> <span class="ͼd">ServerAuditToolkitv2</span></div><div class="cm-line"><br></div><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼe"># Update later</span></div><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">git</span> <span class="ͼd">pull</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10449px; height: 18.8887px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><span>If files are marked as downloaded from the internet:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ4z ͼ3v" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">Get-ChildItem</span> -<span class="ͼd">Recurse</span> -<span class="ͼd">File</span> | <span class="ͼd">Unblock-File</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10449px; height: 18.8887px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>3) Quick Start (TL;DR)</span></h2><p><strong><span>Local server audit</span></strong><span> (run from repo root):</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ50 ͼ3x" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10449px; height: 18.8887px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><strong><span>Multiple servers</span></strong><span> (current user via WinRM):</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ51 ͼ3z" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">ComputerName</span> <span class="ͼd">srv1</span>,<span class="ͼd">srv2</span>,<span class="ͼd">srv3</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10416px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><strong><span>Disable parallelism</span></strong><span> (for low‑spec hosts / diagnostics):</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ52 ͼ41" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">ComputerName</span> <span class="ͼd">srv1</span>,<span class="ͼd">srv2</span> -<span class="ͼd">NoParallel</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10416px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><strong><span>Change output directory</span></strong><span>:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ53 ͼ43" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">OutDir</span> <span class="ͼd">C:</span>\<span class="ͼd">Temp</span>\<span class="ͼd">SATV2</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10419px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><blockquote><p><span>If remoting is disabled or blocked, run the toolkit </span><strong><span>locally</span></strong><span> on each target.</span></p></blockquote><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>4) Outputs &amp; Where to Find Them</span></h2><p><span>After a run, check the </span><code><span>out/</span></code><span> folder:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ54 ͼ45" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">out/</div><div class="cm-line">  data_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json              # full dataset</div><div class="cm-line">  summary_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.md             # quick text summary</div><div class="cm-line">  report_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.html            # Bootstrap dashboard</div><div class="cm-line">  migration_units_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json   # normalized "+what to migrate" units</div><div class="cm-line">  csv/</div><div class="cm-line">    migration_units.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    readiness_findings.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    iis_sites.csv, iis_pools.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    hyperv_vms.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    smb_shares.csv, smb_ntfs_top.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    certificates.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    network_adapters.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    storage_volumes.csv, storage_disks.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    local_users.csv, local_groups.csv, local_group_members.csv</div><div class="cm-line">    printers.csv, printer_ports.csv</div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10419px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><span>Open the HTML report in your browser for a rich view; use CSVs for filtering/slicing.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>5) Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)</span></h2><p><strong><span>A. Pre‑flight checks</span></strong></p><ol data-spread="false" start="1"><li><p><span>Confirm you have admin rights on targets</span></p></li><li><p><span>Confirm WinRM service is running (or plan to run locally)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Ensure enough disk space in the chosen </span><code><span>-OutDir</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>If auditing DHCP: verify access to </span><code><span>ADMIN$</span></code><span> share for fallback export</span></p></li></ol><p><strong><span>B. Execute</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>For a </span><em><span>single</span></em><span> host:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ55 ͼ47" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">ComputerName</span> <span class="ͼd">myserver</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98956px; top: 5.10416px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div></li><li><p><span>For a </span><em><span>list</span></em><span> from CSV (</span><code><span>servers.csv</span></code><span> with header </span><code><span>ComputerName</span></code><span>):</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ56 ͼ49" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">$targets</span> = <span class="ͼd">Import-Csv</span> .\<span class="ͼd">servers</span>.<span class="ͼd">csv</span> | <span class="ͼd">Select</span> -<span class="ͼd">Expand</span> <span class="ͼd">ComputerName</span></div><div class="cm-line">.\<span class="ͼd">src</span>\<span class="ͼd">Invoke-ServerAudit</span>.<span class="ͼd">ps1</span> -<span class="ͼd">ComputerName</span> <span class="ͼd">$targets</span> -<span class="ͼd">Verbose</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98956px; top: 5.10416px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div></li><li><p><span>For constrained targets, add </span><code><span>-NoParallel</span></code><span>.</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>C. Review</span></strong></p><ol data-spread="false" start="1"><li><p><span>Open </span><code><span>out\report_*.html</span></code><span> and scan </span><strong><span>Top readiness findings</span></strong></p></li><li><p><span>Drill into </span><strong><span>Migration Units</span></strong><span> counts and confidence</span></p></li><li><p><span>Export CSVs if you need to hand data to workstreams (DNS/DHCP/IIS/Files/etc.)</span></p></li></ol><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>6) What We Inventory (by collector)</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><strong><span>System</span></strong><span>: OS/build, uptime, hardware basics</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Roles &amp; Features</span></strong><span>: Installed + available (or installed‑only via WMI)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Network</span></strong><span>: NICs, IPs, DNS, routes, firewall (fallback to classic tools)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Storage</span></strong><span>: Disks/volumes/partitions, BitLocker status, Dedup (if present)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>AD DS</span></strong><span>: Forest/domain modes, DCs, FSMO, SYSVOL (DFSR/FRS heuristic)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>DNS</span></strong><span>: Zones, forwarders (module or WMI provider)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>DHCP</span></strong><span>: Scopes/options/lease counts (module; netsh export fallback)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>IIS</span></strong><span>: Sites/bindings/app pools; http.sys SSL (module; appcmd fallback)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Hyper‑V</span></strong><span>: VMs/NICs/disks/switches (module; WMI fallback)</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>SMB</span></strong><span>: Shares + top‑level NTFS ACL snapshot</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Certificates</span></strong><span>: Key LocalMachine stores + http.sys SSL</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Scheduled Tasks</span></strong><span>: Task details and run info</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Local Accounts</span></strong><span>: Users, groups, group membership</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Printers</span></strong><span>: Queues + ports (PrintManagement; WMI fallback)</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>7) Migration Units &amp; Readiness Rules (How We Decide “What to Migrate”)</span></h2><p><strong><span>Migration Units (MUs)</span></strong><span> are normalized items like </span><code><span>DnsZone</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>DhcpScope</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>IisSite</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>HvVm</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>SmbShare</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>Certificate</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>ScheduledTask</span></code><span>, etc. Each has:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><code><span>Id</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>Kind</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>Server</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>Name</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>Summary</span></code></p></li><li><p><code><span>DependsOn[]</span></code><span> (e.g., IIS binding → certificate)</span></p></li><li><p><code><span>Confidence</span></code><span> (module=high; WMI=medium; text fallback=lower)</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Readiness rules</span></strong><span> evaluate MUs to produce findings (e.g., “HTTPS binding without cert”, “Cert expires &lt; 90 days”). Findings are written to </span><code><span>csv/readiness_findings.csv</span></code><span> and shown in the report.</span></p><blockquote><p><span>Engineers triage findings, then plan the migration per role using the MU lists and CSVs.</span></p></blockquote><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>8) Troubleshooting</span></h2><p><strong><span>Access denied / RPC server unavailable</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Ensure admin rights and that WinRM/firewall allow remoting; otherwise run locally on the server.</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>DHCP export fallback fails</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Confirm </span><code><span>\\&lt;server&gt;\ADMIN$</span></code><span> access and free space; re‑run with </span><code><span>-Verbose</span></code><span> and check console output.</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Empty sections (IIS/Hyper‑V/Printers)</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>If the role/module isn’t present, the collector may return via fallback or be empty; verify the server actually hosts that role.</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>HTML loads without CSS</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>The report uses Bootstrap CDN. Content still shows; if you need fully offline HTML, raise an issue to enable a “single‑file” mode.</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Performance</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Use </span><code><span>-NoParallel</span></code><span> on fragile systems.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Split very large server lists into batches.</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>9) Contributing (Engineering Workflow)</span></h2><p><strong><span>Branching</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Create feature branches from </span><code><span>main</span></code><span>: </span><code><span>feat/&lt;area&gt;-&lt;short&gt;</span></code><span> (e.g., </span><code><span>feat/collector-nps</span></code><span>), or </span><code><span>fix/&lt;short&gt;</span></code></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Coding rules</span></strong></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>One collector per file exporting </span><code><strong><span>Get-SAT&lt;Area&gt;</span></strong></code><span> and returning a </span><strong><span>hashtable</span></strong><span> keyed by server</span></p></li><li><p><span>Prefer modern modules; implement </span><strong><span>WMI/command</span></strong><span> fallback</span></p></li><li><p><span>Use </span><code><span>Write-Log</span></code><span> (not </span><code><span>Write-Host</span></code><span>). Don’t mutate system state.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Keep objects lean; avoid unnecessary JSON round‑trips</span></p></li><li><p><span>Add caps for heavy enumerations (e.g., </span><code><span>-MaxAclEntries</span></code><span>)</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Tests &amp; linting</span></strong></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ57 ͼ4b" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">Invoke-Pester</span> -<span class="ͼd">Path</span> .\<span class="ͼd">tests</span> -<span class="ͼd">Output</span> <span class="ͼd">Detailed</span></div><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼd">Invoke-ScriptAnalyzer</span> -<span class="ͼd">Path</span> .\<span class="ͼd">src</span> -<span class="ͼd">Settings</span> .\<span class="ͼd">PSScriptAnalyzerSettings</span>.<span class="ͼd">psd1</span> -<span class="ͼd">Recurse</span></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10417px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><p><strong><span>Pull Requests</span></strong><span> (checklist)</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><br class="ProseMirror-trailingBreak"></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Commit style</span></strong><span> (recommended)</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Conventional commits: </span><code><span>feat: add printer collector</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>fix: dhcp fallback path</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>docs: update runbook</span></code></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>10) Extending SATv2</span></h2><h3><span>A) Add a new collector</span></h3><ol data-spread="false" start="1"><li><p><span>Create </span><code><span>src/Collectors/&lt;NN&gt;-&lt;Area&gt;.ps1</span></code><span> exporting </span><code><span>Get-SAT&lt;Area&gt;</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>Detect capability in </span><code><span>src/Private/Capability.ps1</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>Add function name to </span><code><span>$collectors</span></code><span> in </span><code><span>ServerAuditToolkitV2.psm1</span></code><span> and to </span><code><span>FunctionsToExport</span></code><span> in the </span><code><span>.psd1</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>Return a </span><strong><span>hashtable</span></strong><span> keyed by server; use </span><code><span>Write-Log</span></code><span> generously</span></p></li><li><p><span>Add Pester tests and (optionally) CSV + HTML wiring in </span><code><span>Report.ps1</span></code></p></li></ol><p><span>Collector skeleton:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ58 ͼ4d" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="powershell" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line"><span class="ͼh">function</span> <span class="ͼd">Get-SATExample</span> {</div><div class="cm-line">  [<span class="ͼd">CmdletBinding</span>()] <span class="ͼh">param</span>([<span class="ͼd">string</span>[]]<span class="ͼd">$ComputerName</span>,[<span class="ͼd">hashtable</span>]<span class="ͼd">$Capability</span>)</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼd">$out</span>=@{}; <span class="ͼh">foreach</span>(<span class="ͼd">$c</span> <span class="ͼh">in</span> <span class="ͼd">$ComputerName</span>){</div><div class="cm-line">    <span class="ͼh">try</span>{ <span class="ͼd">Write-Log</span> <span class="ͼd">Info</span> <span class="ͼi">"Example on </span><span class="ͼd">$c</span><span class="ͼi">"</span></div><div class="cm-line">      <span class="ͼh">if</span>(<span class="ͼd">$Capability</span>.<span class="ͼd">HasExample</span>){ <span class="ͼd">$out</span>[<span class="ͼd">$c</span>]=@{ /* <span class="ͼd">module</span> <span class="ͼd">path</span> */ } }</div><div class="cm-line">      <span class="ͼh">else</span> { <span class="ͼd">$out</span>[<span class="ͼd">$c</span>]=@{ /* <span class="ͼd">fallback</span> <span class="ͼd">path</span> */ } }</div><div class="cm-line">    } <span class="ͼh">catch</span> { <span class="ͼd">$out</span>[<span class="ͼd">$c</span>]=@{ <span class="ͼd">Error</span>=<span class="ͼd">$_</span>.<span class="ͼd">Exception</span>.<span class="ͼd">Message</span> }; <span class="ͼd">Write-Log</span> <span class="ͼd">Error</span> <span class="ͼi">"Example failed on </span><span class="ͼd">$c</span><span class="ͼi"> : </span>$(<span class="ͼd">$_</span>.<span class="ͼd">Exception</span>.<span class="ͼd">Message</span>)<span class="ͼi">"</span> }</div><div class="cm-line">  }</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼh">return</span> <span class="ͼd">$out</span></div><div class="cm-line">}</div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10413px; height: 18.8889px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><h3><span>B) Add a readiness rule</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Default rules live in </span><code><span>src/Private/Migration.ps1</span></code><span> (</span><code><span>Get-SATDefaultReadinessRules</span></code><span>) as JSON</span></p></li><li><p><span>Add an object with keys: </span><code><span>id</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>appliesTo</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>severity</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>message</span></code><span>, </span><code><span>when</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>The </span><code><span>when</span></code><span> expression is a PowerShell expression evaluated with </span><code><span>$Item</span></code><span> bound to the Migration Unit</span></p></li></ul><p><span>Example:</span></p><div class="cm-editor ͼ1 ͼ2 ͼ4 ͼ59 ͼ4f" data-is-code-block-view="true" contenteditable="false"><div class="cm-announced" aria-live="polite"></div><div tabindex="-1" class="cm-scroller"><div spellcheck="false" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" translate="no" contenteditable="true" class="cm-content" role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" data-language="json" style="tab-size: 4;"><div class="cm-line">{</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼk">"id"</span>: <span class="ͼi">"hv-vm-paused"</span>,</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼk">"appliesTo"</span>: <span class="ͼi">"HvVm"</span>,</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼk">"severity"</span>: <span class="ͼi">"Medium"</span>,</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼk">"message"</span>: <span class="ͼi">"VM is paused or saved state."</span>,</div><div class="cm-line">  <span class="ͼk">"when"</span>: <span class="ͼi">"($Item.Summary -like '*State=Paused*') -or ($Item.Summary -like '*State=Saved*')"</span></div><div class="cm-line">}</div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-layer-above cm-cursorLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: 150; animation-duration: 1200ms;"><div class="cm-cursor cm-cursor-primary" style="left: 5.98962px; top: 5.10547px; height: 18.8887px;"></div></div><div class="cm-layer cm-selectionLayer" aria-hidden="true" style="z-index: -2;"></div></div></div><blockquote><p><span>(Roadmap) We plan to support external </span><code><span>-RulesPath</span></code><span> so teams can maintain rules per destination (Azure, WS2025, etc.).</span></p></blockquote><h3><span>C) Wire data into the report</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>In </span><code><span>Report.ps1</span></code><span>, create rows, call </span><code><span>Write-SATCsv</span></code><span>, add Quick‑link, and render a small table (limit rows with </span><code><span>$maxHtmlRows</span></code><span>).</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>11) Release &amp; Versioning</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Update </span><code><span>ModuleVersion</span></code><span> in </span><code><span>src/ServerAuditToolkitV2.psd1</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>Tag releases: </span><code><span>vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH</span></code><span> (e.g., </span><code><span>v0.3.0</span></code><span>)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Optional: create GitHub Releases with zipped </span><code><span>src/</span></code><span> and a sample </span><code><span>out/</span></code><span> report</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>12) Security &amp; Data Handling</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Treat outputs as sensitive (IPs, accounts, bindings). Store in restricted locations; avoid emailing raw exports.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If sharing outside the core team, consider a redaction pass (e.g., hash MACs, truncate SIDs) before distribution.</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>13) FAQ</span></h2><p><strong><span>Do I need to install PowerShell 7?</span></strong><span> No, SATv2 targets Windows PowerShell 4.0+.</span></p><p><strong><span>Can I run this without admin rights?</span></strong><span> Partial data may be collected, but many collectors require admin; expect gaps.</span></p><p><strong><span>Remoting is blocked; what now?</span></strong><span> Run locally on each server and copy the </span><code><span>out/</span></code><span> folder back.</span></p><p><strong><span>My report shows “low confidence”. Why?</span></strong><span> That indicates a fallback path (WMI/text). Verify manually before planning.</span></p><p><strong><span>How do I add a destination profile?</span></strong><span> Add rules that reflect the target platform (e.g., App Service or Azure Files) and tag MUs accordingly.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>14) Contacts &amp; Support</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Use GitHub Issues for bugs/requests</span></p></li><li><p><span>For urgent blockers, contact the platform team on the designated channel (add your team contact here)</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><p><span>Happy auditing 🚀</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></section></div></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="0513d4d9-f97c-42b0-b07c-4f4ccc28607b" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hi