 items-start justify-between text-start flex-row"><button class="flex w-full items-center gap-0.5"><span class="font-medium"><span class="flex items-center gap-1 truncate text-start align-middle text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary dark:hover:text-token-text-primary dark:text-[var(--interactive-label-tertiary-default)]" style="opacity: 1;">Thought for 1m 22s<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-rtl-flip="" class="icon-xs"><path d="M7.52925 3.7793C7.75652 3.55203 8.10803 3.52383 8.36616 3.69434L8.47065 3.7793L14.2207 9.5293C14.4804 9.789 14.4804 10.211 14.2207 10.4707L8.47065 16.2207C8.21095 16.4804 7.78895 16.4804 7.52925 16.2207C7.26955 15.961 7.26955 15.539 7.52925 15.2793L12.8085 10L7.52925 4.7207L7.44429 4.61621C7.27378 4.35808 7.30198 4.00657 7.52925 3.7793Z"></path></svg></span></span></button></div></div></span><div class="max-w-[calc(0.8*var(--thread-content-max-width,40rem))]"></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="88cf6896-62af-4950-8059-f28eacf654a0" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="180">Good catch — that error is because <code data-start="35" data-end="50">$PSScriptRoot</code> is coming back <strong data-start="66" data-end="75">$null</strong> in your wrapper script, so <code data-start="103" data-end="114">Join-Path</code> can’t build the default <code data-start="139" data-end="148">-OutDir</code>. Two things are likely at play:</p>
<ol data-start="182" data-end="411">
<li data-start="182" data-end="322">
<p data-start="185" data-end="322">You’re running <code data-start="200" data-end="224">Invoke-ServerAudit.ps1</code> <strong data-start="225" data-end="247">from the repo root</strong>, but the original wrapper assumed it lives in <code data-start="294" data-end="300">src\</code> and built <code data-start="311" data-end="319">..\out</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="323" data-end="411">
<p data-start="326" data-end="411">On some hosts (older PowerShell / certain invocations), <code data-start="382" data-end="397">$PSScriptRoot</code> can be unset.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="413" data-end="602">Below is a <strong data-start="424" data-end="454">drop-in, defensive wrapper</strong> that works whether the file is in <strong data-start="489" data-end="509">repo root or src</strong>, and whether <code data-start="523" data-end="538">$PSScriptRoot</code> is set or not. It also finds the module manifest automatically.</p>
<hr data-start="604" data-end="607">
<h3 data-start="609" data-end="665">Fix: replace your <code data-start="631" data-end="655">Invoke-ServerAudit.ps1</code> with this</h3>
