 w-full flex-col items-start justify-between text-start flex-row"><button class="flex w-full items-center gap-0.5"><span class="font-medium"><span class="flex items-center gap-1 truncate text-start align-middle text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary dark:hover:text-token-text-primary dark:text-[var(--interactive-label-tertiary-default)]" style="opacity: 1;">Thought for 1m 11s<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-rtl-flip="" class="icon-xs"><path d="M7.52925 3.7793C7.75652 3.55203 8.10803 3.52383 8.36616 3.69434L8.47065 3.7793L14.2207 9.5293C14.4804 9.789 14.4804 10.211 14.2207 10.4707L8.47065 16.2207C8.21095 16.4804 7.78895 16.4804 7.52925 16.2207C7.26955 15.961 7.26955 15.539 7.52925 15.2793L12.8085 10L7.52925 4.7207L7.44429 4.61621C7.27378 4.35808 7.30198 4.00657 7.52925 3.7793Z"></path></svg></span></span></button></div></div></span><div class="max-w-[calc(0.8*var(--thread-content-max-width,40rem))]"></div></div></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="4efa03bf-1331-4e49-9f7e-7c9e8bd4c889" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-thinking"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="193">Great call. To include <strong data-start="23" data-end="46">Windows Server 2012</strong> and <strong data-start="51" data-end="85">older PowerShell (down to 2.0)</strong>, here’s a clean retrofit that keeps full fidelity on newer hosts while running best-effort on legacy boxes.</p>
<p data-start="195" data-end="288">I’ve grouped everything into: (1) what changes, (2) drop-in files, and (3) a quick checklist.</p>
<hr data-start="290" data-end="293">
<h1 data-start="295" data-end="323">What changes (at a glance)</h1>
<ul data-start="325" data-end="1367">
<li data-start="325" data-end="665">
<p data-start="327" data-end="343"><strong data-start="327" data-end="343">Target tiers</strong></p>
<ul data-start="346" data-end="665">
<li data-start="346" data-end="423">
<p data-start="348" data-end="423"><strong data-start="348" data-end="358">Tier A</strong> (WS 2016+/PS 5.1): full features (modules + JSON, all CSV/HTML).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="426" data-end="509">
<p data-start="428" data-end="509"><strong data-start="428" data-end="438">Tier B</strong> (WS 2012/2012 R2, PS 3.0–4.0): full features via module/WMI fallbacks.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="512" data-end="665">
<p data-start="514" data-end="665"><strong data-start="514" data-end="524">Tier C</strong> (PS 2.0 / older roles like 2008 R2): <em data-start="562" data-end="575">best-effort</em>: WMI/<code data-start="581" data-end="588">netsh</code>/<code data-start="589" data-end="597">appcmd</code> only, <strong data-start="604" data-end="615">no JSON</strong> (we export <strong data-start="627" data-end="637">CLIXML</strong> instead), UI still renders.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="667" data-end="823">
<p data-start="669" data-end="823"><strong data-start="669" data-end="681">Manifest</strong>: switch to legacy-safe keys (<code data-start="711" data-end="728">ModuleToProcess</code>, remove <code data-start="737" data-end="759">CompatiblePSEditions</code>). Keep <code data-start="767" data-end="794">PowerShellVersion = '2.0'</code> to allow loading everywhere.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="825" data-end="1088">
<p data-start="827" data-end="879"><strong data-start="827" data-end="843">Compat layer</strong>: add <code data-start="849" data-end="861">Compat.ps1</code> with helpers for:</p>
<ul data-start="882" data-end="1088">
<li data-start="882" data-end="931">
<p data-start="884" data-end="931">Safe object creation without <code data-start="913" data-end="931">[pscustomobject]</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="934" data-end="995">
<p data-start="936" data-end="995">JSON/CLIXML export (JSON only when <code data-start="971" data-end="987">ConvertTo-Json</code> exists)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="998" data-end="1046">
<p data-start="1000" data-end="1046">Safe service/module checks (no <code data-start="1031" data-end="1035">?.</code> operators)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1049" data-end="1088">
<p data-start="1051" data-end="1088">Small utility shims (PS 2.0-friendly)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1090" data-end="1232">
<p data-start="1092" data-end="1232"><strong data-start="1092" data-end="1106">Collectors</strong>: keep module paths, but ensure a <strong data-start="1140" data-end="1155">WMI/command</strong> fallback in every collector and <strong data-start="1188" data-end="1219">remove any JSON round-trips</strong> inside them.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1234" data-end="1367">
<p data-start="1236" data-end="1367"><strong data-start="1236" data-end="1247">Wrapper</strong>: write via <code data-start="1259" data-end="1275">Export-SATData</code> (JSON if available, else CLIXML), and keep the robust <code data-start="1330" data-end="1343">$ScriptRoot</code> logic you already have.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1369" data-end="1372">
<h1 data-start="1374" data-end="1391">Drop-in updates</h1>
