<hr data-start="6487" data-end="6490">
<h2 data-start="6492" data-end="6543">6) Collector coding style adjustments (PS2-safe)</h2>
<p data-start="6545" data-end="6625">You <strong data-start="6549" data-end="6558">don’t</strong> need to rewrite everything. Apply these small, global conventions:</p>
<ul data-start="6627" data-end="7208">
<li data-start="6627" data-end="6700">
<p data-start="6629" data-end="6700">Replace <strong data-start="6637" data-end="6665"><code data-start="6639" data-end="6663">[pscustomobject]@{...}</code></strong> with <strong data-start="6671" data-end="6699"><code data-start="6673" data-end="6697">New-SATObject @{ ... }</code></strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6701" data-end="6802">
<p data-start="6703" data-end="6802">Replace <strong data-start="6711" data-end="6735"><code data-start="6713" data-end="6720">Where</code> short syntax</strong> with full: <code data-start="6747" data-end="6778">Where-Object { $_.Installed }</code> (no <code data-start="6783" data-end="6800">Where Installed</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6803" data-end="6881">
<p data-start="6805" data-end="6881">Remove any <strong data-start="6816" data-end="6841"><code data-start="6818" data-end="6822">?.</code> null-conditional</strong> uses; do classic <code data-start="6859" data-end="6880">if ($x) { $x.Prop }</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6882" data-end="7029">
<p data-start="6884" data-end="7029">Remove <strong data-start="6891" data-end="6930"><code data-start="6893" data-end="6928">ConvertTo-Json | ConvertFrom-Json</code></strong> normalization inside collectors. Just return raw arrays/hashtables; remoting already deserializes.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7030" data-end="7136">
<p data-start="7032" data-end="7136">For <strong data-start="7036" data-end="7055">Scheduled Tasks</strong> on PS2, always use <code data-start="7075" data-end="7103">schtasks /Query /V /FO CSV</code> fallback (module may not exist).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7137" data-end="7208">
<p data-start="7139" data-end="7208">For <strong data-start="7143" data-end="7162">Network/Storage</strong>, prefer WMI path when <code data-start="7185" data-end="7207">$cap.PSVersion -lt 3</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<blockquote data-start="7210" data-end="7341">
<p data-start="7212" data-end="7341">Practical tip: do a one-time find-and-replace pass on <code data-start="7266" data-end="7284">[pscustomobject]</code> and the <code data-start="7293" data-end="7300">Where</code> shorthand across <code data-start="7318" data-end="7340">src/Collectors/*.ps1</code>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="7343" data-end="7346">
<h2 data-start="7348" data-end="7389">7) What degrades on PS 2.0 (by design)</h2>
<ul data-start="7391" data-end="7898">
<li data-start="7391" data-end="7495">
<p data-start="7393" data-end="7495"><strong data-start="7393" data-end="7401">JSON</strong>: no built-in <code data-start="7415" data-end="7436">ConvertTo/From-Json</code> → we export <strong data-start="7449" data-end="7459">CLIXML</strong> instead. HTML + CSV still produced.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7496" data-end="7622">
<p data-start="7498" data-end="7622"><strong data-start="7498" data-end="7518">NetTCPIP/Storage</strong>: use <strong data-start="7524" data-end="7547">WMI + classic tools</strong>. You still get adapters/IPs/routes/firewall and disks/volumes via Win32_*.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7623" data-end="7721">
<p data-start="7625" data-end="7721"><strong data-start="7625" data-end="7657">LocalAccounts/ScheduledTasks</strong>: always fall back to <code data-start="7679" data-end="7701">WMI + net localgroup</code> and <code data-start="7706" data-end="7720">schtasks.exe</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7722" data-end="7801">
<p data-start="7724" data-end="7801"><strong data-start="7724" data-end="7735">Hyper-V</strong>: WMI <code data-start="7741" data-end="7762">root\virtualization</code> (v1) on older hosts (2012 or 2008 R2).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7802" data-end="7898">
<p data-start="7804" data-end="7898"><strong data-start="7804" data-end="7813">AD DS</strong>: .NET DirectoryServices + <code data-start="7840" data-end="7855">netdom/nltest</code> fallback if the AD module isn’t installed.</p>
</li>
</ul>
